Most commentators suppose that Ennius utters these verses himself, and that the distress alluded to was oc- casioned by the infamous conduct of the brother os Flamininus, who was expelled in consequence from the senate by Cato, at that time censor, B.C. 184 (Lim, xxxix„ 42).
